10 March Acting Minister in The Presidency, Khumbudzo Ntshavheni will tomorrow brief media on the outcomes of the Cabinet meeting held on Wednesday, 10 March  2021. The Minister of Higher Education, Science and Innovation , Dr Blade Nzimande will join the media briefing virtually to unpack the decision taken by cabinet on the National Student Financial Aid Scheme (NSFAS) process. The details of the briefing are as follows:Date: Thursday, 11 March  2021Time: 11h00Venue: GCIS – Ronnie Mamoepa Press Room, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Francis Baard Street, Hatfield, Pretoria. Media Participation: Journalists may view the briefing via live streaming on the South African Government social media channels on the links below:Facebook: http://facebook.com/GovernmentZA  Twitter: http://twitter.com/GovernmentZAYouTube: https://www.youtube.com/user/GovernmentZA Enquiries:   Phumla Williams, Cabinet SpokespersonCell: 083 5010 139